  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Mrs. Mary Merrick Brooks has heard from Mr. (Charles Lenox) Remond that the Hutchinsons will not sing at the New England Convention. And feeling certain that &quot;there are many put out&quot; who would attend if these singers were advertised to be there, she pleads with Maria Weston Chapman for special efforts to secure their presence. Mary M. Brooks was &quot;made glad by the report of the national society.&quot;</subfield>
